quran[35]{c,v,t}:
  26,70,"when he said to his father and his people, 'What do you serve"
  26,71,"They said, 'We serve idols, and continue cleaving to them"
  26,72,"He said, 'Do they hear you when you call"
  26,73,"or do they profit you, or harm"
  26,74,"They said, 'Nay, but we found our fathers so doing"
  26,75,"He said, 'And have you considered what you have been serving"
  26,76,"you and your fathers, the elders"
  26,77,"They are an enemy to me, except the Lord of all Being"
  26,78,"who created me, and Himself guides me"
  26,79,and Himself gives me to eat and drink
  26,80,"and, whenever I am sick, heals me"
  26,81,"who makes me to die, then gives me life"
  26,82,and who I am eager shall forgive me my offence on the Day of Doom
  26,83,"My Lord, give me Judgment, and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,and appoint me a tongue of truthfulness among the others
  26,85,Make me one of the inheritors of the Garden of Bliss
  26,86,"and forgive my father, for he is one of those astray"
  26,87,Degrade me not upon the day when they are raised up
  26,88,the day when neither wealth nor sons shall profit
  26,89,except for him who comes to God with a pure heart
  26,90,And Paradise shall be brought forward for the godfearing
  26,91,and Hell advanced for the perverse
  26,92,"It shall be said to them, 'Where is that you were serving"
  26,93,apart from God? Do they help you or help themselves
  26,94,"Then they shall be pitched into it, they and the perverse"
  26,95,"and the hosts of Iblis, all together"
  26,96,"They shall say, as they dispute there one with another"
  26,97,"By God, we were certainly in manifest error"
  26,98,when we made you equal with the Lord of all Being
  26,99,It was naught but the sinners that led us astray
  26,100,so now we have no intercessors
  26,101,no loyal friend
  26,102,"O that we might return again, and be among the believers"
  26,103,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,104,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"